  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex transactions or legitimate businesses. Legal definitions typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal definitions vary by jurisdiction, but most involve:\n- Concealing the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Transforming criminal proceeds into seemingly legitimate assets\n- Attempting to make illegal money appear legal\n- Intentionally disguising the origins of criminal proceeds\n\nPenalties often include:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional sanctions\n\nThe exact specifics depend on national and international anti-money laundering (AML) laws.",
